name: Framed Street Irregulars — 008
description:
"Framed Street Irregulars" is an experimental series by LEMSSS in which he uses algorithms and javascript code techniques to display his Black & White Street Photographs into a generative 1:1 video style of stills. A series of a nostalgic video that will give you an experience to watch an image like you're traveling to a memory from the past.

The base of the sound that you hear from this piece was made using a tool that analyses the image information to which then translates it to various note that creates the sound. Then I used the generated sound as the base and added few effects such as reverb.

----

— Resolution 2304x2304
— Format MP4
— Images made with P5js and Native Javascript
— Base sound made with PIXELSYNTH (Olivia Jack)
— Duration: 120 seconds
